  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The-- the-- the-- the Jewish Committee-- the-- the-- I can't even remember exactly, to the Haganah that-- and to the agents throughout Europe, wherever they were able to buy a ship, they would buy a ship, however small it was or however big it was.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But most of the problems, and perhaps the main problem, was not just the ship itself, because business is business.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anybody will sell, and anybody would buy that had the money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To buy a ship was much easier.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But to conceal-- to conceal the purchasing of that ship so that the British intelligence that was always in-- working in order to find out, where are the Jews loading the next ship for Palestine.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because they had the British Navy on their side, the British intelligence.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had the British Air Force working for them to-- to patrol the seas, the coast of Europe to find out if they can pinpoint any illegal ship and then advise the navy to go and-- and-- and stop that ship.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And stop they did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were many, many ships that, however unseaworthy they were, they were sent back to the high seas.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When they were close to Palestine, and when they-- when they could see the shores of Eretz Israel, they were not allowed to disembark.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know, many thousands of people died because of it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If there's anything that-- that really aggravates me about the British government, the policies, was to ship-- to send the ships back to the high seas when they really had no right to do it, absolutely no right, no human right.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was inhumane.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But our function in the Haganah was to help when we were notified.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
